Cell["\<\
The condition number of a matrix is a measure of how sensitive the solution \
of a linear system is to small changes in the input data. It quantifies the \
numerical stability of matrix operations and is defined as the ratio of the \
largest to the smallest singular value of the matrix.\
\>", "Notes",
 CellID->2095288529,ExpressionUUID->"8ef7ad8c-a569-40c4-8097-c286d6057dd0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Implementation note: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["MatrixConditionNumber"]], 
    "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/MatrixConditionNumber", 
    "QuantumMob Package Symbol"},
   "PackageLink",
   BaseStyle->"InlineFormula"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "77d0c91a-8ce8-48bb-bcbc-7d5c9605a72b"],
 " is based on ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["SingularValueList"]], "paclet:ref/SingularValueList"},
   "RefLink",
   BaseStyle->{"InlineFormula"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "c8d33b7c-3df0-4a47-ab08-860f0d2306d4"],
 ", and gives the 2-norm condition number."
}], "Notes",
 CellID->806001884,ExpressionUUID->"2cb8363d-bd2a-4b2b-93ac-9312961300d8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "For a large approximate numerical matrix, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{
      Cell[
       TextData["LUDecomposition"]], "paclet:ref/LUDecomposition"},
     "RefLink",
     BaseStyle->{"InlineFormula"}], "[", 
    StyleBox["mat", "TI"], "]"}], "[", 
   RowBox[{"[", "3", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "f83c734d-ac77-4ae9-b25a-2b6bc06ff343"],
 " may calculate an estimate of the condition number give about 3 times \
faster than the current implementation. However, remember that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{
      Cell[
       TextData["LUDecomposition"]], "paclet:ref/LUDecomposition"},
     "RefLink",
     BaseStyle->{"InlineFormula"}], "[", 
    StyleBox["mat", "TI"], "]"}], "[", 
   RowBox[{"[", "3", "]"}], "]"}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "144a9da1-6442-4907-818b-f38e67c7516e"],
 "  always gives 0 for a matrix in exact numbers and returns the \
\[Infinity]-norm condition number."
}], "Notes",
 CellID->79380119,ExpressionUUID->"a2fbd076-819b-4637-aaed-ab78b4037883"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "With ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   TemplateBox[{
     Cell[
      TextData["Tolerance"]], "paclet:ref/Tolerance"},
    "RefLink",
    BaseStyle->{"InlineFormula"}], "\[Rule]", 
   StyleBox["t", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "f8b96cb5-6b21-4b14-bcc7-ab918af8e045"],
 ", singular values that are smaller than ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox["t", "TI"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "d9e386be-1515-4e10-91d1-bd995a97dd73"],
 " times the largest singular value are regarded zero. That is, the ratio ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   StyleBox["min", "TI"], "/", 
   StyleBox["max", "TI"]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "d07bde27-a447-4913-bb06-3dc99a016a57"],
 " of the smallest to largest singular values is regarded zero (the condition \
number is \[Infinity])."
}], "Notes",
 CellID->1260834000,ExpressionUUID->"b387730e-cbf2-4047-ae33-d7c200160b92"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "With ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\"\<Standard\>\"", "\[Rule]", 
   TemplateBox[{
     Cell[
      TextData["False"]], "paclet:ref/False"},
    "RefLink",
    BaseStyle->{"InlineFormula"}]}]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "481ee599-c93c-4b32-8c56-fb48bfc8d7a2"],
 ", only ",
 StyleBox["non-zero",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " singular values are considered. Therefore, the condition number may be \
finite even for a singular matrix. This finite number is highly useful when \
solving least-squares problems or underdetermined systems where a traditional \
inverse does not exist, but a stable \"best-fit\" solution is still needed. \
It measures how sensitive the solvable, non-zero parts of your system are to \
errors."
}], "Notes",
 CellID->1947313170,ExpressionUUID->"777249ea-093b-4b2b-83aa-62f3b39adeea"]
}, Closed]],

